def: Terrifying; frightful.-- Af*fright"ful*ly, adv. [Archaic]Bugbears or affrightful apparitions. Cudworth.
A kind of bread made of the meal of maize (Indian corn), mixedwith water or milk, etc., and baked. [U.S.] J. Barlow.
A thin, flying cloud; a rack.
Of or pertaining to Mecca, in Arabia.-- n.
One of the ventral processes of a vertebra, or the dorsalelement in each half of a hemal arch, forming, or corresponding to, avertebral rib.-- Pleu*rap`o*phys"i*al, a. Owen.
Bearing signs. [Obs.] "The signifer sphere, or zodiac."Holland.
A species of coarse linen, originally made in Osnaburg,Germany.
